content:
I was trying to bisect an issue and this happened:

...
searched toolchains nightly-2021-08-21 through nightly-2022-01-01


********************************************************************************
Regression in nightly-2021-09-22
********************************************************************************

fetching https://static.rust-lang.org/dist/2021-09-21/channel-rust-nightly-git-commit-hash.txt
ERROR: Tarball not found at https://static.rust-lang.org/dist/2021-09-21/channel-rust-nightly-git-commit-hash.txt

Is there a way around this/is this an expected error?

It looks like there were no nightly artifacts produced on 2021-09-21. It's possible there was a hiccup in the release server that day.

I personally would just look at the commits between those two days and see if any of them look relevant to what you are bisecting. The list should be at https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/compare/5ecc8ad8462574354a55162a0c16b10eb95e3e70...ac2d9fc509e36d1b32513744adf58c34bcc4f43c
If there isn't anything obvious, then you can manually bisect the range using rustup-toolchain-install-master.
With rustup-toolchain-install-master, you can give it specific sha commits to download.
